threat_severity.level_description: Severity HIGH because it was considered trojan. Other contributing factors were that it matches yara rules with files that have detections and it could not be run in sandboxes.

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: YARA rule to detect if a sqllang.dll version is targeted by skip-2.0. Each byte pattern corresponds to a function hooked by skip-2.0. If $1_0 or $1_1 match, it is probably targeted as it corresponds to the hook responsible for bypassing the authentication.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: Mathieu Tartare <mathieu.tartare@eset.com>

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects modules used by DEEPDATA based on the required export names used by those modules.
crowdsourced_yara_results.author: threatintel@volexity.com

crowdsourced_yara_results.description: Detects generic strings across multiple DEEPDATA plugins, a malware family from the BrazenBamboo threat actor.
